Mental Health: diagonosed with severe depression

We have spoken with Bernard a couple of times about his chronic lateness (ranging from 5min to 25min late at times); he suffers from severe depression and it is very difficult for him to get up in the mornings, but he makes the effort to get to the Roulant on time.

He has said that volunteering with us is like a lifeline for him, very therapeutic, life changing; we have agreed to accommodate his lateness as long as he continues to make the effort to show up on time

We have spoken with him about challenges involving his pace of work vs the time he spends chatting with other volunteers and taking long breaks; he agreed to work on these things in order to focus more on the task at hand so the work he is given gets done on time. (Bertha's Note, Imported July 2021)

jo4388823674.note:
POUR LA FERME
Mes moyens de transports seront plus restreints pour le mois de juin, je n'aurai accès qu'à Communauto pour me rendre à la ferme. Cela pourrait restreindre mes disponibilités, en fonction du coût et de la disponibilité des véhicules (qui rendront probablement plus difficile les appels de dernière minute, mais j'ai quand même coché, on sait jamais!). Par contre, puisque le cout est le même selon que j'utilise les véhicules toute la journée, où seulement pour l'avant-midi, je pourrais rester toute la journée si c'est possible. 

À partir du mois de juillet, je devrais normalement avoir accès au véhicule de mon copain plus facilement, et donc avoir moins de contraintes de déplacement.

POUR L'AGRICULTURE URBAINE
Aucune contrainte de ce type, je me déplace à Bixi :-) Très intéressé par ce nouveau projet mystérieux du jardin de la Cité des Hospitalières!

AUTRES PROJETS
À terme je pourrais être intéressé par d'autres projets (entre autre la cuisine et les conserves), mais pour le moment, la covid me rend moins à l'aise pour les activités intérieures. 

MES MOTIVATIONS
J'ai quitté récemment un emploi en programmation de jeux vidéos. Je cherche en ce moment à réorienter ma vie vers des activités qui soient plus en cohérence avec mes valeurs sociales et environnementales. L'agriculture me tente depuis plusieurs années, mais à noter que je n'ai aucune (comme dans zéro!) expérience! Je suis très enthousiaste à l'idée de faire de nouveaux apprentissages.

zh5145717897.note:
Peter volunteers for deliveries mostly. Below are lines of communication that the vol program would like you to use with him so we stay consistent as a team. These often repeat!

The vol program doesn't want Peter going alone on routes, as such being a passenger in a car is not ideal. There has been instances where he has gone in to the wrong apartments or has gotten confused with directions, leading to meals not being delivered to the clients. It's best if he is accompanied by a strong volunteer. Please use this line of communication with Peter if he asks to go in a car (he is often pushy to go again):
-"We may put you on a car only if the pairing is right, and only on a day where Chelsea or Ellen are on BD/SL to assist with co-navigating over the phone."

Peter will often ask to show up late or to leave early. Please use this line of communication for this request:
-"Sorry Peter, we can only put your name on the schedule if you can commit to being on time and staying for the full shift. We can't predict if it will be a busy day."

Peter will ofter ask to sign up for a shift and say something like "I might be free that day". Please use this luine of communication to address that:
-"Sorry Peter, it's less helpful for us if you sign up and cancel last minute. We only want you signing up if you can be sure to commit to the shfit. Please call later in the week when you know your schedule."
